translation[7]{c,v,t}:
  9,62,"Yeh log tumhare saamne kasmein khate hain taa-ke tumhein raazi karein, halanke agar yeh momin hain to Allah aur Rasool iske zyada haqdar hain ke yeh unko raazi karne ki fikr karein"
  9,63,Kya inhein maloom nahin hai ke jo Allah aur uske Rasool ka muqabla karta hai uske liye dozakh ki aag hai jismein woh hamesha rahega. Yeh bahut badi ruswayi hai
  9,64,"Yeh munafiq darr rahey hain ke kahin musalmano par koi aisi surat nazil na ho jaye jo inke dilon ke bhed khol kar rakh de. (Aey Nabi), insey kaho, “aur mazaq udao, Allah us cheez ko khol dene wala hai jiske khul janey se tum darte ho”"
  9,65,"Agar insey pucho ke tum kya baatein kar rahey thay, to jhat keh denge ke hum to hansi mazaq aur dil lagi kar rahey thay. Insey kaho, “kya tumhari hansi dil lagi Allah aur uski aayat aur uske Rasool hi ke saath thi"
  9,66,"Ab uzraat (excuses) na tarasho, tumne iman laney ke baad kufr kiya hai, agar humne tum mein se ek giroh ko maaf kar bhi diya to dusre giroh ko to hum zaroor saza denge kyunke woh mujreem hai.”"
  9,67,"Munafiq Mard aur munafiq auratein sab ek dusre ke hum-rang hain, burayi ka hukum dete hain aur bhalayi se mana karte hain aur apne haath khair se roak rahey hain. Yeh Allah ko bhool gaye to Allah ne bhi inhein bhula diya, yaqeenan yeh munafiq hi fasiq hain"
  9,68,"In munafiq mardon aur auraton aur kafiron ke liye Allah ne aatish e dozakh ka wada kiya hai jismein woh hamesha rahenge, wahi inke liye mauzun(proper place) hai, inpar Allah ki phitkar hai aur inke liye qayam rehne wala azaab hai"